Our Technology

What We Do

From partnerships with the NHS and Roche to at-home testing, ScanX is revolutionising point of care testing to make healthcare more accessible, affordable, and targeted to the people who really need it, where they need it.



Clinical Testing

ScanX services with key NHS trusts and other clinical partners to provide ClearScreen, an accurate and fast lateral flow and urine dip reading, recording, and reporting solution. Simple implementation and deployment of the ClearScreen app on camera-enabled mobile devices.



At-Home Testing

Our Technology

ScanX's focus is about accessibility and usability. To achieve this, our revolutionary proprietary technology works in three simple steps.

Step 1

Scan

The user (whether a healthcare professional or a layperson at home) uses the mobile app to support correct performance of the test.

The user (whether a healthcare professional or a layperson at home) uses the mobile app to support correct performance of the test.

Step 2

Analyse

Our powerful analysis software provides a computer vision-read test result.

Our powerful analysis software provides a computer vision-read test result.

Step 3

Integrate

The result and other user-input data is now digitally available to be shared with doctors, pharmacies, and integrated into electronic patient records or other organisational systems.

The result and other user-input data is now digitally available to be shared with doctors, pharmacies, and integrated into electronic patient records or other organisational systems.

Clinical Settings

Clinical Settings

Partnerships

Pharmacies



Implementation

  • 

  • Low cost: the ClearScreen app runs on camera-enabled devices that you have in situ. ScanX can also provide devices as part of your package, as well as stands, cables, and any other infrastructure desired.

  • 

  • Training materials provided: these can be added to your LMS or provided through our portal.

  • 

  • Integrations: unidirectional integrations with several middleware solutions - no direct access to the Electronic Medical System (EMS) is required. We can integrate into any private system with minimal data risk. No patient data is stored in the app.



Ongoing Support

  • 

  • In-person and remote support both during implementation and for the life of the solution.

  • 

  • Healthcare professionals onsite who understand workflow challenges and can support with ensuring staff adoption.

  • 

  • Regular updates to include features and functionality based on user feedback.
